Key Match Events: The NY Mets rally in the 9th inning with Pete Alonso hitting a game-winning three-run home run, followed by Jesse Winker's steal and Starling Marte's double to secure the 4-2 victory over the Milwaukee Brewers.
Post-Match Reflections: The Mets advanced to the NLDS after their win, setting up a future matchup against the Philadelphia Phillies.
